	<p><em><strong>Richard Dyason</strong> replies:</em> Firstly, Australia is not my 'adpted' country - I hate it.</p> <p>Secondly I too feel disenfranchised, but DO vote in Australia - Laobor(sic) of course.</p> <p>Thirdly, I will be returning to the beautiful country of England in September this year. My wife and I are having a narrowboat built in Mirfield West Yorkshire. We shall also be puchasing a home in the UK.</p> <p>All of this paid for by the Australian Governmnet - Quite a laugh eh?</p>
	<small>
